# veriva-eval: API keys for the LIVE judge demo (`npm run eval`) and `npm run bench`.
# The zero-key replay demo (`npm run replay`) needs NONE of these.
#
# Copy to .env and fill in whatever you have. The judge auto-detects which keys
# are present and runs the panel with the available models, skipping the rest.

# --- One key, whole panel (recommended) -------------------------------------
# OpenRouter exposes models from every vendor behind a single key, so the judge
# can run a true cross-FAMILY panel (Anthropic + OpenAI + Google ...) with one
# account. If this is set, it takes precedence over the native keys below.
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=

# --- Or native provider keys ------------------------------------------------
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
OPENAI_API_KEY=
GOOGLE_API_KEY=

# --- Optional model-id overrides --------------------------------------------
# Defaults target current frontier models. If a default id is stale for your
# account, override it here (ids change faster than this repo does).
# JUDGE_MODEL_CLAUDE=claude-sonnet-4-6
# JUDGE_MODEL_OPENAI=gpt-5.1
# JUDGE_MODEL_GEMINI=gemini-2.5-pro
# OPENAI_BASE_URL=https://api.openai.com/v1

# --- Competitor benchmark (`npm run bench`, optional) -----------------------
# Hold the base model constant across providers so the benchmark isolates the
# orchestration framework, not the model:
# BASELINE_MODEL_KEY=claude          # which panel model the `baseline` provider uses (default: first available)
# QODO_MODEL=anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6   # the model pr-agent runs (any litellm id)
# QODO_COST_CENTS=6                  # coarse per-review cost estimate for the comparison
